  "texts": [
    "Correspondingly, y = [y 1, y 2,..., y 2N] ∈ R 2N represents the real-valued counterpart of x, obtained by decomposing each complex sample into its real and imaginary parts.",
    "Specifically, the first N elements of y correspond to the real parts of x, while the remaining N elements correspond to the imaginary parts.",
    "Conditioned on h, the sequence {y n } 2N n=1 consists of i.i.d.",
    "real-valued samples, each distributed as y n |h ∼ N (0, σ 2 xi /2) since the real and imaginary components of x n equally share the total variance.The conditioned PDF of y given the variance of the transmitted bit, σ 2 i, and h is expressed asf Y y|σ 2 i, h = 2N n=1 1 πσ 2 xi exp - y 2 n σ 2 xi.",
    "(3)The MLD rule, denoted by L, for symbol variance detection can be expressed asL ≜ p(y | σ 2 0, h) p(y | σ 2 1, h) σ 2 1 ≶ σ 2 0 Pr(σ 2 1) Pr(σ 2 0), (4)where Pr(σ 2 0) and Pr(σ 2 1) are the a priori probabilities of sending bit 1 and bit 0, respectively."
